OL,3,CGrant Shapps distances himself from
OL,4,CAnderson's comments about Khan
OL,6,Fthe London mayor had "given our
OL,7,Fcapital city away to his mates", with
OL,8,Fprime minister facing calls from
OL,9,FLabour for Mr Anderson to lose the
OL,10,Fwhip.
OL,12,FMr Shapps, the defence secretary, told
OL,13,FITV News that he had not listened to
OL,14,Fthe MP for Ashfield's comments, but
OL,15,Fsaid: "In this country we maintain
OL,16,Famazingly good, for the most part,
OL,17,Fcommunity relations.
OL,19,F"It doesn't matter whether you're
OL,20,FChristian, Jewish or Muslim, and I
OL,21,Fwant to see that continued.
