OL,3,CGrant Shapps distances himself from
OL,4,CAnderson's comments about Khan
OL,6,F"I have many concerns and complaints
OL,7,Fabout the London mayor who I think has
OL,8,Fbeen terrible for transport, terrible
OL,9,Ffor housing and hasn't been good for
OL,10,Fpolicing, but I wouldn't use that kind
OL,11,Fof language about him either.
OL,13,F"In the end we have the perfect
OL,14,Fopportunity to rid the capital of
OL,15,FSadiq Khan - it's an election and it
OL,16,Fcomes in May."
OL,18,FMr Shapps said the outcome of the
OL,19,Fmatter was one for "others" in the
OL,20,FConservative party to decide.
